## BMAD Workflow (MANDATORY)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Always use BMAD story-driven development. Never implement directly from high-level requests.

**Before starting any work:**

1. Read `bmad/qf-bmad/workflows/bmad-flow.md` for orchestration phases
2. Create/consume stories in `bmad/epics/<epic>/stories/`
3. Attach deliverables and handoff notes to each story
4. Run QA validation before marking complete

**After completing any story (MANDATORY):**

1. Update story file `Status:` field to `✅ Complete` (or `⚠️ Partial`)
2. Add `**Completed**: YYYY-MM-DD` to story header
3. Mark Definition of Done checkboxes as `[x]`
4. Add Completion Notes section with implementation details
5. Update epic overview status table

> ⚠️ Work is NOT complete until story status is synchronized with code state.

