## BMAD Quick Commands

| Command | Compute Level | Purpose |
|---------|---------------|---------|
| `/bmad <topic>` | Maximum | Full 5-phase orchestration with parallel agents |
| `/epic <name>` | Medium | Create new epic with context gathering |
| `/refine <epic>` | Targeted | Gap analysis on existing epic |
| `/story <path>` | Focused | Create or implement a story |
| `/feature <name>` | Setup | Create isolated worktree, switch Claude to work in it |
| `/implement <path>` | Execution | Full implementation of epic or stories until complete |
| `/think <question>` | Deep | Sequential reasoning without BMAD structure |
| `/explore <topic>` | Research | Max-compute codebase exploration |
| `/review [depth]` | Validation | Code review with auto-detected or specified depth |
| `/configure` | Setup | Auto-detect project settings from codebase |
| `/simplify [path]` | Cleanup | Analyze and reduce code complexity |

